The paper discusses the application of deep learning models to time series forecasting, specifically for electric load forecasting. This topic falls under the machine learning and artificial intelligence fields, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The use of recurrent neural networks and sequence to sequence models also suggests that the paper may fall under the cs.NE sub-category, which covers neural and evolutionary computing. The focus on efficient operations in critical infrastructure suggests that the paper may also fall under the cs.SY sub-category, which covers systems and control. Finally, the use of signal processing techniques in deep learning architectures suggests that the paper may also fall under the cs.SE sub-category, which covers signal processing.
